(30, 'en', 'admincp', 'phpfox', '2.0.0alpha1', 'setting_drop_down_example', 'Separate drop downs with commas. The first drop down will be the default drop down. (Example: drop1, drop2, drop3)', 'Separate drop downs with commas. The first drop down will be the default drop down. (Example: drop1, drop2, drop3)', 1213993229),
(31, 'en', 'admincp', 'phpfox', '2.0.0alpha1', 'setting_add_var', 'The <b>Variable</b> of your new setting is how you will identify and call this specific setting and return the given value.\r\n\r\nIf you create a <b>Variable</b> with <b>foo</b> it can be used later within the PHP script as:\r\n[php]\r\necho App::getParam(''foo'');\r\n[/php]\r\nThe above code will print out the value of foo.\r\n\r\nNote that if you add spacing or unsupported characters (alphanumeric support only) to your <b>Variable</b> it will automatically be renamed to fit the standards, which we will replace all unsupported characters or spaces with an underscore.', 'The <b>Variable</b> of your new setting is how you will identify and call this specific setting and return the given value.\r\n\r\nIf you create a <b>Variable</b> with <b>foo</b> it can be used later within the PHP script as:\r\n[php]\r\necho App::getParam(''foo'');\r\n[/php]\r\nThe above code will print out the value of foo.\r\n\r\nNote that if you add spacing or unsupported characters (alphanumeric support only) to your <b>Variable</b> it will automatically be renamed to fit the standards, which we will replace all unsupported characters or spaces with an underscore.', 1213994889),
